<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-17106] JMS requestTimeout seems to be ignored</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-17106</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I was looking at the CI and code trying to understand why this test&#160; &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;1&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; runs so much slower than the others (~20 secs) and I noticed something strange. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Despite being configured to use 1 sec as the timeout &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;2&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;, the value seems to be ignored and the request nonetheless times out only after 20 secs. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Modifying the template&apos;s requestBody call to override the timeout using the CamelJmsRequestTimeout header seems to work-around the issue (and apparently fixes the test slowness as well). &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/camel/blob/8cd6b34e8bc753520f3153a354beb9765e3f2741/components/camel-jms/src/test/java/org/apache/camel/component/jms/JmsRouteRequestReplyTest.java#L407&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/camel/blob/8cd6b34e8bc753520f3153a354beb9765e3f2741/components/camel-jms/src/test/java/org/apache/camel/component/jms/JmsRouteRequestReplyTest.java#L407&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;


